cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.IT, cs.CY

This paper deals with the topic of network routing and path diversity in the context of the Internet. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses security implications, which could place it in the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) category. The use of IP geolocation and geographical mapping could also make it relevant to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) category. Additionally, the paper proposes a quantitative measure for geographical diversity, which could place it in the cs.IT (Information Theory) category. Finally, the paper discusses the implications of its findings for network resilience, which could make it relevant to the cs.CY (Computers and Society) category.
